<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06057051 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06057051 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  NEW-JERSEY; PROFESSIONAL; HOCKEY; GAME; RESULT  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  John MacLean had three goals and an assist Monday night to lead the New JerseyDevils to a 5-1 victory over the Washington Capitals in East Rutherford, N.J.;   The win gave the Devils a five-point lead over Washington in the race forthe fourth and final playoff spot in the Patrick Division. Both teams have 16games left.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  MACLEAN'S THREE GOALS SPARK DEVILS  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  NHLRoundup  </MEMO><TEXT>     The Capitals gave away the puck twice in their zone in the first period,leading to goals by Jon Morris and MacLean.;    MacLean stretched the lead to3-0 at 7 minutes, 31 seconds of the second period, tipping ViacheslavFetisov's shot past goalie Jim Hrivnak with 28 seconds left on a five-minutehigh-sticking penalty to Kent Paynter.;    After a goal by New Jersey's LaurieBoschman made it 4-1, Mike Liut replaced Hrivnak. MacLean then capped off hissecond three-goal game of the season and sixth of his career with 5:04 left inthe period.;    MacLean, who had 27 goals in the first 40 games of the season,had only six in the next 23 before Monday night's outburst.;  RED WINGS 5,MAPLE LEAFS 4: Yves Racine scored at 1:26 of overtime to give Detroit ahome-ice victory over Toronto.;    Racine took a pass from Bob Probert andfired a slap shot past Leafs goaltender Jeff Reese, negating Toronto'scomeback from a 4-2 deficit with less than nine minutes left in the thirdperiod.;    The victory snapped Detroit's six-game winless streak.;  CANUCKS4, FLAMES 2: Trevor Linden and Dan Quinn scored 48 seconds apart in the secondperiod to spark Vancouver to a home-ice victory over Calgary.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910226  </PUBDATE> <DAY> 